Exercises

1.length of a list
2.sum of the elements of a list
3.sum of the even numbers of a list
4.sum of the elements on even positions in a list
5.existence of an item in a list
6.position of an item in a list, if it exists in it
7.counter for an item in a list
8.maximum element in a list (recursion with local variables)
9.reverse a list (recursion with accumulators)
10.interpolate lists
11.generate list from 1 to a given n
12.shift right in a list (e.g. shiftr [1,2,3,4] ==> [4,1,2,3])
13.shift left
14.remove first occurence of an element in a list
15.remove all ocurrences of an element in a list
16.remove the n first ocurrences of an element in a list
17.remove the last ocurrence of an element in a list
18.switch one element for another in a list (first ocurrence)
18.switch one element for another in a list (all ocurrences)
19.switch one element for another in a list (n first ocurrences)
20.return lasts element of a list
21.returns lists w/o its last element
22. shift right n times
23. shift left n times